China continued to see a generally stable housing market in December 2021, with home prices in 70 major cities showing slight month-on-month decrease, official data showed on Saturday. New home prices in four first-tier cities, that is Beijing, Shanghai, Shenzhen and Guangzhou, edged down 0.1 percent month on month in December, according to data from the National Bureau of Statistics. A total of 31 second-tier cities saw a month-on-month decrease of 0.3 percent in new home prices, while those in 35 third-tier cities also fell 0.3 percent last month.